 the struggles of Chinese and Jewish survivors who managed to cultivate memory through inimical times and preserve the continuity of their long traditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311053801440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014405540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300144055423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300144055/original  a978-3-11-053801-4  Yale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  a978-3-11-064968-0  Asian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Package  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles